              representation space. The probe identifies a linear transformation
              under which squared L2 distance encodes the distance between words
              in the parse tree, and one in which squared L2 norm encodes depth
              in the parse tree. Using our probe, we show that such
              transformations exist for both ELMo and BERT but not in baselines,
              providing evidence that entire syntax trees are embedded
              implicitly in deep models' vector geometry.},
	author = {Hewitt, John and Manning, Christopher D},
