               complexity of the task increased over the course of the
               experiment. Our results demonstrated higher reaction times in the
               right compared to left hand ( p = 0.0004). Movements became
               increasingly curved and erroneous with cognitive load, but
               interlimb differences in movement quality were absent. We found
               higher joint cocontraction in the right compared to left arm ( p},
	author = {Jayasinghe, S A L},
	journal = {J. Neurophysiol.},
