@misc{Gambi2017-qb,
	abstract = {Summary To what extent are linguistic representations shared
               between production and comprehension? What is the nature of the
               links between production and comprehension processes? In this
               chapter, we provide an introduction to those models that
               incorporate explicit assumptions about the degree of sharing and
               review some supporting evidence. We show that full sharing of
               representations is uncontroversial only for semantics and syntax,
               while there is mixed evidence over the degree of overlapping at
               the level of phonological and phonetic representations. We then
               propose a taxonomy of production-comprehension links, ranging
